We are recruiting for a Group Revenue Manager to join our team. The Group Revenue Manager will be responsible for ensuring that revenue is capitalised in all revenue centres across the group, by means of thorough analysis and review, and the implementation of techniques and strategies, as necessary. The Group Revenue Manager will oversee the revenue team across the Collection, and will develop a positive and collaborative working relationship with the Group Sales &amp; Marketing Manager, the General Managers and the Revenue team.
<br /><br />
The successful candidate will primarily be based in Head Office, Wexford Town and must be available to travel between all properties.
<br /><br />
<b>Main Duties:</b><br />
To ensure effective systems of yield management are in place and that maximum revenue is achieved on any given day in all properties;
<br />To ensure best practice revenue management across the group in terms of yield management, revenue build, rate parity, distribution, OTA’s etc.
<br />Thoroughly analyse each revenue stream to ensure revenue in each property is being capitalised, starting with accommodation but broadening to, bars, restaurants; conference &amp; banqueting, weddings and leisure clubs in time;
<br />To assess overall business goals and review and develop an effective revenue strategy across the Collection to ensure the achievement of same, both in the medium and long-term.
<br />To lead, manage and develop the revenue teams across the Collection to ensure all are working in synergy towards property and group revenue strategy;
<br />To foster a culture of positivity, productivity, result orientation and collaboration within the revenue management team across the properties;
<br />To train and grow the revenue team encouraging continuous development and progression;
<br />Prepare an outline for and support the annual revenue budget process, in conjunction with the Group Financial Controller and Managing Director;
<br />Support the achievement of property sales turnover and annual budgets by means of an effective revenue strategy;
<br />To have monthly meetings at property level with the General Manager, Sales &amp; Marketing Manager and Reservations/Revenue Manager ensuring the common pursuit of business targets and business goals;
<br />To have regular meetings with the Group Sales &amp; Marketing Manager encouraging a synergy and common goal approach between the Revenue and Sales &amp; Marketing functions;
<br />To conduct a competitor analysis regularly, ascertaining business and revenue generation and growth, taking fluctuating market demands into consideration;
<br />Responsible for the maintenance and management of our revenue management system to include training the relevant teams;
<br /><br />
<b>Requirements:</b><br />
5 years plus revenue management experience within a hotel group;
<br />Responsibility for revenue management of a cluster or multiple properties is desirable;
<br />5 years plus experience leading and managing a team to achieve results;
<br />Revenue management qualification would be an advantage;
<br />Must be a strategist and have excellent analytical skills;
<br />Must have excellent interpersonal and leadership skills;
<br /><br />
Outstanding package on offer for the right candidate, in the range of €60k-€70 per annum &#43; exceptional company benefits.
